    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "there are some things the validator could check and what is actually checked is client-dependent and I don't know the latest here for each client\r\n\r\nthere are some things the validator cannot check e.g. transaction validity and it trusts the relay to only allow valid transactions\r\n\r\nyou should be very careful about which relays you connect to and moreover should understand that things are still pretty early for the mev-boost ecosystem so there is a much higher chance of bugs etc which could mean loss of revenue as a validator\r\n\r\nif you don't feel like you understand all of the risks I would try to learn more about them and hold off on running any external builder software until you know better what could happen",
